#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.110"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.110:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.110:0.2"
msgid "11. Phāsuvihāravagga"
msgstr "11. Living Comfortably"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.110:0.3"
msgid "110. Araññasutta"
msgstr "110. Wilderness"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.136"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.110:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ araññavanapatthāni "
"pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when a mendicant has five qualities they’re ready to frequent "
"remote lodgings in the wilderness and the forest."

msgctxt "an5.110:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.110:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with "
"good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they "
"keep the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an5.110:1.4"
msgid "bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;"
msgstr ""
"They’re very learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These "
"teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the "
"end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s "
"totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering "
"them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with "
"right view."

msgctxt "an5.110:1.5"
msgid ""
"āraddhavīriyo viharati thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu "
"dhammesu;"
msgstr ""
"They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and "
"gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking "
"off when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "an5.110:1.6"
msgid ""
"catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī "
"hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī;"
msgstr ""
"They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that "
"belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty."

msgctxt "an5.110:1.7"
msgid ""
"āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

msgctxt "an5.110:1.8"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu alaṃ "
"araññavanapatthāni pantāni senāsanāni paṭisevitun”ti."
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant has these five qualities they’re ready to frequent remote "
"lodgings in the wilderness and the forest.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.110:1.9"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.110:1.10"
msgid "Phāsuvihāravaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.110:2.1"
msgid "Sārajjaṃ saṅkito coro,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.110:2.2"
msgid "Sukhumālaṃ phāsu pañcamaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.110:2.3"
msgid "Ānanda sīlāsekhā ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an5.110:2.4"
msgid "Cātuddiso araññena cāti."
msgstr ""
